The paper discusses the creation and performance comparison of a Beowulf cluster using commodity hardware, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel computing (cs.SC). The use of MPI and MPICH for coding also suggests a focus on parallel programming (cs.PL). The motivation for creating a small and cheap device for students and researchers indicates a potential focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
